The paper discusses improvements in the usability and security of secure email, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on user interface design, which suggests a potential fit for human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the practical application of secure email for ordinary users, which could fall under the category of cyber security (cs.CY). The use of tutorials and instructional interfaces also suggests a potential fit for software engineering (cs.SE) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
